cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper deals with a problem of cross-modal object recognition with robotic active exploration, which involves computer vision, machine learning, and robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses finding a common representation, defining features, transferring features, and classifying objects, which are typical tasks in computer vision and machine learning, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions human ability and an experiment with participants, indicating cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as a possible sub-category.
